This video was very difficult to describe. Mainly because there was no dialogue between the characters, just the voiceover. I was trying to imagine what the characters would be like in real life and the interactions they would have. I listened to the voiceover and tried to pair their thoughts and movements with what the voiceover was doing. That made it easier to remember and explain.

I think the experiment was trying to measure how people explain scenarios, interactions and settings where there are no real life human characters. Especially when these characters aren't properly communicating or having conversations, the whole story is being dictated by a voiceover.
